commentTextItems.html: cross bat shot down the ground, it's all over, crowd swarm onto the ground and mob the NZ batsmen

commentPostTextItems.html: no doubt Steve Waugh will whinge that the crowd aren't paying any attention to him this time
great win for NZ, that goes someway towards avenging that painful defeat at Chennai in 1996
and some scary approximation of a haka is being performed by a bunch of shirtless guys in front of the dressing room
and now hopefully people will stop saying Australia are favourites despite all evidence to the contrary
Waugh says he isnt all that worried abou the way they're playing....
Fleming says it one of his most memorable victories as captain
but says they must be consistent
and Twose is the Man of the match, 80 not out off 99 balls
big day for the World Cup tomorrow, a credit to the schedulers in that they see WI v Bangladesh as important enough to devote a day to
this will be the 1st ODI for WI against an associate country since *that* match at Pune, coverage as per usual will start at 945 GMT
